    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Joseph Thomas Ellis owned a general store that conducted business in Amherst County during the late nineteenth century.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>John Thomas Ellis Daybooks, 1885-1887, of a general store operated by John Thomas Ellis record in chronological order merchandise purchased by individual customers. Entries list name of customer, items purchased, amount owed, and amount paid. Items purchased include soap, clothing, knives, coffee, and various types of food.
</p>
      <p>John Thomas Ellis Ledgers, 1881-1888, of a general store operated by John Thomas Ellis record the debts and payments of individual customers.
</p>
    </scopecontent>
